parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel seizes or locks
and the vehicle may shut off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to respond
the vehicle fails to start
the vehicle stalls
the security pass lock and anti-lock warning indicators randomly flash intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the anti-theft system warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle fails to start
the ignition key pulls out while the engine is still running
the vehicle can be turned off without the key turning to the off position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring and lighting system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The lights
radio
and dashboard lights malfunction
the headlights do not work
the rear passenger side tail lights fail
the windshield transmission wiper linkage bushing fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat adjustment system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The seat motor runs but cannot make seat adjustments
the seat sags to the right when trying to move forward or back.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat frame can cause the seat to become unstable, leading to a loss of control while driving, which can result in accidents or injuries. Additionally, the seat belt may not function properly, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver's seat wobbles
tilts
or drops down
the seat frame breaks or welds fail
the seat leans to one side
the seat moves while driving
the seat belt may not function properly.
